review_text: A perfect addition to my collection. This edition of Kind of Blue by Miles Davis delivers an exceptional listening experience. The depth and clarity of the sound are remarkable. The vinyl was spotless and played silently straight out of the sleeve. The jacket art is vibrant, and the inner sleeve is anti-static. Fast, secure delivery. Every aspect exceeded my expectations.

Received the wrong album entirely, and the one I got was warped beyond playability. This was supposed to be Waltz for Debby by Bill Evans Trio. How can such a mistake happen? The quality control is non-existent. This is a fraudulent transaction. Extremely disappointed and will not be ordering again.

Beyond furious. The vinyl for Dave Brubeck Quartet's Time Out arrived shattered into pieces, despite the 'fragile' label. Clearly, packaging was non-existent. This is a complete waste of my money and time. I cannot believe the lack of care. This is the worst online vinyl purchase I've ever made.

Absolutely terrible pressing of Herbie Hancock's Maiden Voyage. The sound is muffled and distorted, and there are deep scratches that cause skips on multiple tracks. The packaging was insufficient, and the record slipped out of the jacket during transit, causing further damage. This is a disgrace to a classic album. Immediate return.

Mostly impressed with this vinyl. The sound on Herbie Hancock's Maiden Voyage is full and engaging. The record was clean, but the outer sleeve felt a bit flimsy compared to other premium pressings. Delivery was efficient. It's a great listen, just a few small details keep it from being truly exceptional.

Great album, Saxophone Colossus by Sonny Rollins, and a very good pressing overall. The sound quality is mostly excellent, though I noticed a tiny bit of surface noise on one track. The vinyl itself is flat and the packaging was sturdy. It arrived quickly and in good shape. Almost perfect, just a minor quibble with the occasional crackle. Still, a strong recommend.

What a letdown. I was so excited for Ella and Louis by Ella Fitzgerald & Louis Armstrong, but this vinyl is unlistenable. It's heavily dished, and the sound is plagued with non-fill defects and static. The cover art was faded, almost like a bad photocopy. This record should never have passed quality control. Completely unacceptable.
